50|$|A CAdES-based {{electronic}} signature is accepted {{in a court}} proceeding as evidence; as advanced {{electronic signature}}s are legally binding.8 But it gets he higher probative value when enhanced to a <b>qualified</b> <b>electronic</b> signature. To receive that legal standing, {{it needs to be}} doted with a digital certificate, encrypted by a security signature creation device ("qualified electronic signature"). The authorship of a statement with a <b>qualified</b> <b>electronic</b> signature cannot be challenged - the statement is non-repudiable.|$|R
